SIMPLE: pontifical
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Pontifical
<hw>Pon*tif"ic*al</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>pontificalis</ets>: cf. F. <ets>pontifical</ets>. See
<er>Pontiff</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Of or pertaining to a pontiff,
or high priest; <as>as, <ex>pontifical</ex> authority</as>; hence,
belonging to the pope; papal.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Of or pertaining to the building of bridges.</def>
<mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Now had they brought the work by wondrous art⟦br⟧
<qex>Pontifical</qex>, a ridge of pendent rock⟦br⟧
Over the vexed abyss.</q> <rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pontifical</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Pontifical
<hw>Pon*tif"ic*al</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A
book containing the offices, or formulas, used by a pontiff.</def>
<rj><au>South.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <pluf>pl.</pluf> <def>The dress and ornaments of a
pontiff.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧Dressed in full <xex>pontificals</xex>.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Sir W. Scott.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pontificality</ent>⟦br⟧
